Seventeen miners who weremissing in a copper mine fire were found today and efforts wereunderway to rescue them and 29 others who were trapped but safein an underground lunch room, officials said.    The mine's owner, Noranda Inc., said one miner died in thefire, six miners escaped unharmed, 29 made it to an undergroundlunch room, where they had air and water, and 17 were laterfound safe in other lunch rooms. Reuter&#3;